Locations.15:
OPPONENT PADDLE TEAMS
STANDARD OPERATING PROCEDURES
COVID-19

All members and guests shall observe the Board of Governors’ overall criteria for returning and Club policies. Our goal is to safely and responsibly have members play paddle at the Club. Masks must be worn in all Racquets common areas and courts at all times.


Prior to Arriving at the Club
1.	All food and beverage is not permitted on League play nights. 
Arriving at the Club
1.	Players must arrive no more than 15 minutes prior to their match time.
2.	Masks must be worn in all Racquets common areas and can only be removed once on the paddle court.
3.	The Paddle Hut will be minimally accessible for members to access the court lights and heaters, only.
4.	The Myopia (tennis area) locker rooms will only be available for restroom and locker/changing usage. Members & guests will not have access shower facilities. 
5.	Water and water refill stations will not be available. Players are encouraged to bring their own prefilled water bottles.
6.	The firepit and grill we be removed.

Playing Paddle
1.	For all emergencies or questions when a staff member is not on site, please bring and use your cell phone. Utilizing house phones is not permitted. This will be the only allowed use of personal cell phones. 
•	Racquet Sports Shop, 617-456-3950
•	Front Desk, 617-566-0240


After playing paddle, all players will have 15 minutes to depart from Club property.
